about.summary: Thin wrapper around the "aws" command line interface for use with LocalStack

name: awscli-local
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "awscli-local" %}
{% set version = "0.4" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: a6a34cc7dd6774194cf43e67a6b93006fb4b395ac0dd5c9245da1b365c8ef767

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - awscli
    - localstack-client
    - python

test: 
  commands: 
    - awslocal -h  # [not win]

about:
  home: "https://github.com/localstack/awscli-local"
  license: "Apache-2.0"
  license_family: "APACHE"
  license_file: "LICENSE"
  summary: "Thin wrapper around the \"aws\" command line interface for use with LocalStack"
  doc_url: "https://pypi.org/project/awscli-local/"
  dev_url: "https://github.com/localstack/awscli-local"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mwilson8
    - oblute
    - benhuff
